#### **Day 39: DOM Manipulation (Part 1)**

```markdown
# Day 39: The Document Object Model (DOM)

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. What is the DOM? (Tree structure of HTML).
2. Selecting elements: `getElementById`, `querySelector`.
3. Changing content: `innerText` vs `innerHTML`.
4. Changing styles via JS.

**Learning Summary:**
The DOM is the bridge between HTML and JavaScript. I learned how to "grab" an element from the HTML page using JS and modify it. `querySelector` is very powerful because it uses CSS selectors (like `.class` or `#id`) to find elements. I wrote a script to change the text of a heading.

**Code Snippet:**
```html
<h1 id="main-heading">Old Text</h1>
<button onclick="changeText()">Change Text</button>

<script>
    function changeText() {
        // Selecting the element
        const heading = document.querySelector("#main-heading");
        
        // Modifying content
        heading.innerText = "Hello JavaScript World!";
        
        // Modifying style
        heading.style.color = "blue";
        heading.style.fontFamily = "Arial";
    }
</script>
